                        WILLIAM GLASS
                  . (Police sergeant, C 3). I produce a certificate—(Read: "Central Criminal Court; Edward Crawford, Convicted, May, 1856, of Larceny; 
Confined nine months")—I was present—the prisoner is the person—he tried to prove an alibi on that occasion also, and failed—I tried to find him after this robbery, but could not, at any of the places where he used to be—he is the constant associate of thieves.





                        JOHN WIRE
                  . (Policeman, F 117). I produce a certificate—(Read: "Guildhall Sessions, Thomas Reid, Convicted April, 1855, of housebreaking and larceny; 
Confined eighteen months")—I was present—the prisoner is the person—I was not engaged in the case, but he was confined at our station before his trial, and I had an opportunity of seeing him there.





                        WILLIAM KING
                  . (Policeman, H 22). I produce a certificate—(Read: "Clerkenwell Sessions; James Adams, Convicted, Sept., 1856, of housebreaking and larceny; 
Confined six months")—Bone is the person—I had him in custody, and was present at the trial.

